On Thu, 11 Nov 1999, Alan Cox wrote:
> > Ehrm, I suffer from the __tiny__ problem that my computer doesn't boot
> > properly with the v2.3.xx kernels... This is because of a bug in the
> > ibmmca SCSI driver... Most annoying.
> 
> Describe ... 8)
Well... The kernel boots, the ibmmca SCSI-driver starts probing drives,
and BOOM, it panics... Same panic every time, too.
IBM MCA SCSI: ERROR - command error!
              Last SCSI-command=0x0, ldn=6, host=0.
IBM MCA SCSI: Subsystem Error-Status follows:
              Command Type................: 30
              Attention Register..........: e6
              Basic Control Register......: 1
              Interrupt Status Register...: e6
              Basic Status Register.......: 4
              SCB End Status Word.........: 2c1
              Command Status..............: 1
              Device Status...............: 0
              Command Error...............: 0
              Device Error................: 0
              Last SCB Address (LSW)......: 4b50
              Last SCB Address (MSW)......: fe
              Send report to the maintainer.
Kernel panic: IBM MCA SCSI: Fatal errormessage from the subsystem!
I haven't pinpointed what kernel the problems began in; I tried v2.3.13
(or was it 14?) without problems, but v2.3.24 (quite a step...), 25 and
26 won't boot.
